15/12/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- On Friday (13 December), President Boris Trajkovski announced he will convene a 26 December meeting of the leaders of the parties that signed the Ohrid peace accord. The four signatories - VMRO-DPMNE, the Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia, the Democratic Party of Albanians and the Party of Democratic Prosperity - are to consult and review implementation of the accord. Representatives of the international community will also be invited. The Democratic Union for Integration will also participate as a member of the government. (MIA, A1 TV - 13/12/02)
